5/5  rDev +11.6%look: 5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5This review is of the 2014 vintage.  I'll be honest about my bias up front: this is my favorite beer, period.  Pours pitch black with a mocha head.  Smell is complex, with hints of chocolate, licorice, coffee, and cherry.  Taste is equally complex, with the coffee of the nose receding a bit as the cherry expands into a deeper, richer, dark fruit taste.  Like many good, complex beers, the complexity only expands as the beer warms.  Mouthfeel is thick and rich, like an imperial stout of this caliber should be.  After trying the initial 4-5 ounces in isolation, I had the remainder paired with a dark chocolate-cardamom-cherry-ginger cake.  This beer is a meal (with dessert) in itself, so no need to pair, but if so, it definitely matches complex, savory desserts well.  Could not recommend more highly. 807 charactersLAp, Sep 12, 2015
