A stout with an “old ale” edge. This beer is the perfect example of how a good beer can taste terrible when it is served too cold. Let this baby warm up to fully appreciate its depth and complexity. This beer brings back faint memories of dark chocolate covered cherries with too much bourbon.  4.5
A – Pours black with red highlights and a two-finger frothy reddish brown head. Head dissipates a bit too quick (-). Not viscous. Great lacing with prominent alcohol legs. 4.5
S – Roasted malts, faint fruitiness and sweetness that almost made me think the beer was infected before I had a taste. Hint of dark chocolate and vanilla. 4.0
T – Deeply roasted malts, an obvious lack of sweetness, a late bitterness that creeps up on you at the back of your mouth and in the throat that includes a very oaky finish. I can taste and even feel the alcohol. 4.5
