5/5  rDev +11.6%look: 5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5Opened a 2015 last night, felt I should use my Deschutes teku. 
Look: Dark as the night, thick as used motor oil. The head is a wonderful dark chocolate brown, like when you'd make ovaltine, but put WAY more than the container suggests. 
Smell: Dark, roasty malts, a bit of tang from the wine barrels, and a bitterness from the huge amount of dark malts present. 
Taste: Oh man, just how I like it. Dark, heavy, a little bit of bourbon, and then the wine barrel comes through. 
Feel: Perfect viscosity, oily and smooth, but the wine barrel keeps it from becoming too heavy. 
Overall: I obviously love this beer. It's quite good, and pretty easy to find. If you like beers with so much dark malts that it borders on bitter, you'll love this. Oh, and for some of the reviewers who said stuff like, "I can't taste the cherry bark!" well, I sure as hell don't know what cherry bark tastes like, and I'm even more sure that you don't either. 941 charactersivegot3Dvision, Apr 15, 2015
