3.73/5  rDev -16.7%look: 4 | smell: 3.5 | taste: 3.75 | feel: 4 |  overall: 3.752014 vintage. Pours black with basically no light getting through; fluffy khaki head that leaves great retention and decent lacing. The aromas are chocolate forward with hints of oak. Tons of cherry and dark fruits. The wine barrels are present. The bourbon barrels, not so much. The flavors seem pretty complex and have alot going on. Lots of milk chocolate with subtle hints of vanilla. More cherry. There's a very subtle tartness going on. Very earthy. Tons of wood/oak characteristics. Tons of molasses. It's on the sweeter side, but it's not cloying. There's hints of dark chocolate and black coffee that gives this one a subtle bitterness that cuts down on some of the sweetness. It finishes with lots of BBQ smoke, probably coming from the cherry bark. Mouthfeel is nice. It's full-bodied with moderate carbonation. Very smooth and fluffy. Alcohol basically goes unnoticed. It's not hot or boozy. Dangerously drinkable.
This is a nice stout. I like it, but I'm not blown away by it. I am blown away by how smooth this is at 11% though. It's a complex brew. I feel the oak wine barrels dominate. The bourbon is subtle. 1,125 charactersBB1313, Feb 11, 2015
