4.37/5  rDev -2.5%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.25Poured from 22 oz bomber into tulip glass,  2013 vintage. 
A:  Just like the name implies, this sucker is pitch black.  No light penetration at all.  Very dense 2-3 finger dark tan head that seems to last forever, and never completely diminishes. Plenty of sticky lacing left behind.
S:  Deep roasted malts, rich espresso beans, bitter dark chocolate, vanilla, molasses, and sweet bourbon.  There are some subtle charred oak notes here also.
T:  Again, lots of deep roasted flavors going on here.  Coffee, chocolate, molasses, and vanilla.  Reminds me of eating dark Swiss chocolate and sipping on strong espresso next to a roaring campfire.
M:  Full bodied but not heavy.  Fairly heavily carbonated for a big stout, and finish is a touch bitter and slightly dry.
O:  Excellent stout that hits on all of the notes that I enjoy. I look forward to cellaring my 2014 bottle for later. 886 charactersrichj1970, Dec 15, 2014
