4.17/5  rDev -6.9%look: 4.25 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.25Long-time want has just been satisfied thanks to your-ad-here.  Here goes:
A:  Nice.  Pours a relatively small head, but it lingers and leaves adequate lacing.  Beer is not perfectly black, however.  There's a noticeable reddish tint when held up to light.
S:  Very good, but more of a dark-fruit stout than a roasted-coffee/chocolate variety.  Some coffee gives way to dark fruit, plum and some vanilla.  Overall a very sweet blend, but nothing that I haven't gotten from other beers.
T:  Again, very good.  Taste follows the nose.  Some charred malt followed by a basket of dark fruit: plum, raisin, cherries and figs.  Also a very winey taste lingers at the back of the palate.  
F:  Good, but not as thick as it should be, IMHO.
O:  A very good stout.  However, I prefer the coffee/chocolate stouts over the dark-fruit varieties, so to me this beer is just "good." 875 charactersleantom, Oct 26, 2014
