4.81/5  rDev +7.4%look: 4.75 | smell: 5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75Poured from a bomber into a stemmed tulip glass and shared with friends
2012 Vintage; poured 2014/06/22
A: Now that is a dark beer! Pours midnight, thick, opaque black with an impressive 2 fingers of everlasting mocha colored head that eventually settles to dense, creamy color leaving a curtain of lace in its wake. 
N: A massive nose on this beast! Massive malt nose, dark roasted malts, dark chocolate, boozy bourbon, vanilla, licorice and some alcohol.
T: The flavor here is so complex. Massive roast malt, espresso, dark chocolate, mild bourbon, vanilla, a touch of hot alcohol, leather, tobacco. The finish is loooong and actually dry out with a great hop bitterness to clean the palate.
M: There is a full body with nice carbonation resulting in a rich, silky-smooth, creamy beer.
O: This is such a tasty brew. All the various barrel treatments have added such depth and flavor making this a real treat. 915 charactersmtomlins, Jun 27, 2014
