1.25/5  rDev -72.1%look: 2.5 | smell: 1.25 | taste: 1 | feel: 2 |  overall: 1Tastes infected. All I'm getting is a wine flavor. Huge disappointment because I usually talk up this beer106 charactersAdmbmb92, Jun 26, 2014
3.75/5  rDev -16.3%look: 3.75 | smell: 3.75 | taste: 3.75 | feel: 3.75 |  overall: 3.75rspauldi, Jun 26, 2014
4.47/5  rDev -0.2%look: 5 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Re-review:
Initially had this in 2013 on tap at Binny's in Lincoln Park. Wasn't particularly impressed; granted, it was served cold and I didn't have time to let it warm as much as I typically like, but the beer itself didn't do much to standout as something so worthy of acclaim. I had been wanting to try it for a while, and was highly disappointed when it didn't rival BCBS to my taste. Good, solid, BA beer, but didn't do anything special for me.
However, I gave it a second try yesterday; a place nearby had 2012 on tap, and I figured, what better to do than give it a re-try when it's had a couple years to age? Good choice.
Served in a snifter, the beer is black, with a beautiful half-inch of brown head; looks great. 
The smell is complex, but I'm having trouble picking up what's going on (mostly because of previous expectation, I think). With that being said, I'm mostly concerned with taste, so let's see how it goes.
Taste: Huh. Still not as sweet as I'd like, but there IS something here! The bourbon barrel portion of this isn't blowing me away, but the pinot noir part is really nice, and gives the beer a distinctly berryish wine flavor. Very elegant, and interesting enough to drink in its own right. There's little to no heat from the barrels, and the beer is smooth throughout your mouth.
I'll admit, while this still didn't blow me away the second time, I get why people love it. Not my favorite if I'm going for a straight BA stout, but if I'm in the mood, I can see really enjoying this for the unique wine spit they've put on it. Nice job from Deschutes; glad I finally get it. 1,608 charactersSeanBond, Jun 26, 2014
