4.68/5  rDev +4.5%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75Had both the 2011 and 2012 on tap at the Red Cow in Minneapolis as part of a Deschutes flight.
Pours a deep, deep brown to black, completely opaque with a thick brown head. Lots of sticky lacing on the flight glass. A rich toasty, roasty aroma with lots of malt and dark fruit on the nose. The 2011 is almost perfect in taste so I'll give it that score. Toasted malt, with minimal hops, sweet with faint molasses on the tastebuds. The 2012 still needs a little more maturation to reach this point, but it's well on its way there. As for the mouthfeel, this is one chewy m-f- of a brew, a meal in itself. Full bodied is just the beginning.
