4.58/5  rDev +2.2%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75The Abyss 2011 vintage 
Deschutes Brewery
Imperial Stout 
11% ABV 
APPEARANCE: As soon as I started to pour and it had that thick gurgle of blackness slowly coming out I new I was going to enjoy this beer. Very small mocha head that kinda danced around before it dissipated into nothingness. 
AROMA: Label pretty much describes the nose to a T. Molasses, slight licorice, dark fruits, chocolate and some nice oakiness. The nose is a little muted but still overall very nice. 
TASTE: Get that barrel right off the bat, oak, vanilla, the dark fruits cherry currants, some wine tannins swirling around as well. Chocolate it very prevalent, dark, light and coca. Not getting much of the licorice which I was looking forward too. As I drink more I get charred oak and coffee that really rounds it out nicely. 
MOUTHFEEL: Thick and syrupy, full bodied light carbonation. The alcohol heat gets you on the finish to let you know what you are drinking. This is so smooth and has a great overall mouthfeel. 
OVERALL: Truly great beer, layers really starting showing as it warms. The abyss has lived up to its hype. Delicious, highly recommend getting into this stout. 
RATING: 4.6/5 Zombie Heads! 1,192 charactersBeerZombies1, May 04, 2014
