4.56/5  rDev +1.8%look: 5 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 5 |  overall: 4.5Been looking forward to trying this for a long time; despite the tumult of praise I've heard, I'm managed to avoid the bottle that's been sitting in my fridge for 4 months. Today is the day, and I'm encouraged by the simple quote on the inside of the waxed cap: "Bravely done". You too, Mr. Beer, you too. Onward! Pours the most delightful thick and syrupy black I, one of the heaviest I have seen. Smell is not super in your face, but some lighter notes than typify stouts. I got lots of cherry, raisin, vanilla, bread and molasses. Taste is wonderful, loaded with toasted oats, sweet tobacco, coffee and some cherries and grapes at the end. Huge flavor from start to finish, leaving some roasted goodness to linger. There is a very slight hint of some tartness, and it works well especially with the slightly higher than average carbonation, for the style. Feel is heavy, and smooth. Coats your entire mouth. 
