4.55/5  rDev +1.6%look: 4 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.52008 Reserve, poured into snifter.
Acquired this one through a trade thinking it would be more recent and with the expectation of aging for a while, but was shocked to see it was a 2008! I've been looking forward to this one for quite some time.
A: Pours a very dark black with just shy of 1 finger of tan head that reduces slowly and leaves little to no lacing. Does not appear to be quite as thick as I had anticipated for the style and ABV, but still clearly has a good body.
S: Aroma wafts with a very rich complex profile. I definitely get a lot of charred/burnt oak on the front, then chocolate, coffee, slight molasses.
T: The flavor of this beer is easily one of my favorites for the style. Nothing is overpowering, and yet I can detect oh so much throughout the glass. I get the charred oak as the strongest flavor, with an amazing balance of chocolate, bourbon, molasses. I get an after taste of smoke that lingers ever so delicately. I love the way everything blends together so well. I haven't had this fresh, but I can only imaging the aging on this beer has done it wonders.
M: Feels slightly thicker than how it appears. Carbed very well.
O: I tremendously enjoyed this one. It comes together so well through the aroma and flavor. I'll certainly be seeking another couple out - I'd like to try one that doesn't have the age on it to see how it compares. Very well done Deschutes! 1,396 charactersroger617, Nov 02, 2013
