Served in 4 sifters with family for a birthday celebration at 55 degrees
A - Beautiful pour at 55 degrees and let it warm as I drank. been aged for three years. thought this would be a proper first review. Beautiful thick, dark pour with a small brown head
S - One of the most amazing smelling beers I've had ahead of Parabola and BCBS and various other Stouts of this caliber. Chocolatey, coffee, carmel, molasses, tasty smell
T - Taste as it smells, alcohol well hidden, very drinkable, THE BEST beer i've had so far at my young age of 22. Twas a good 600th unique beer and one that I will be buying many more of. Very tasty chocolate, coffee, carmel, sweetness.... again so easy to drink
M - For my personal preference of stouts this is as good as it gets.... creamy smooth, i love the bourbon taste of the booze but this wasnt there and for this beer it fit it perfectly.. how can you say anything bad about this beer if you are a stout fan. Hands down the most tasty and drinkable IS i have had
O - There's not much that can be better about this beer. I would be interested in comparing a 2012 to a 2010 as the alcohol was so mellow and hidden. I want to snatch this beer up wherever I can find it and would be willing to pay big $ for getting this beer. With that being said I will! Living in the midwest is a drag for trying to acquire these various amazing stouts.
This one goes in the books as matching my preference perfectly for a stout. Will be buying and again many of these and can't wait to try my Dark Lord that is in route :) to compare these two beers. I have a feeling The Abyss will stand out above all. 1,643 charactersdrmcleod10, Oct 14, 2013
