4.58/5  rDev +2.2%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.52011 Reserve 
A: Pours near pitch black. Sits like a black hole in the glass with a rich, creamy mocha head. 
S: Incredibly rich and robust. A lot of layers and very complex. Rich dark chocolate, anise, espresso, some vinous grape skin, some oaky vanilla and vanilla bean. The natural chocolate and coffee are enhanced greatly by all the barrel aging and other ingredients. 
T: Substantially bitter - dark chocolate, anise, heavily roasted coffee beans, and ash. The vanilla is more subtle than in the nose but still noticeable and rounds out some of the bitterness. The barrel aging components come through very subtly, most prominent is the wine, get little to no bourbon.
P: Medium and incredibly smooth. Very soft carbonation. Leaves a layer of ashy roasty film on the mouth. 
O: The extravagant recipe yields an enhanced RIS that's balanced perfectly. Coming into it I thought it was going to be over the top and was curious about the purpose of the very specific and considerably minute aging, but it worked very well. A fantastic beer 1,047 characterstimc100, Jul 13, 2013
