The smell is very interesting. The first whiff is a sweet dark chocolate smell that I guess is the molasses coming through first. As the beer sits I pick up a little bit of a tart smell which I guess is the wine barrel aging. There is definitely a lot going on here. 
The taste is great. Smooth as smooth gets. Nice sweet taste upfront. One major knock on it is that the warmer it gets the more bitter it becomes. Not bad but just not as good as when its a bit cooler which is the opposite of the others in this category. 
