4.62/5  rDev +3.1%look: 4.5 | smell: 5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5bomber (22oz) served in a snifter.
2010 vintage with a "best after" date of 11/15/11.
300th review.
pours your standard imperial stout-used motor oil black while yielding 3/4" of a thick, creamy, mocha toned head. retention is very respectable for the style, as is the lacing. the nose is mouth-watering: big bold notes of chocolate, coffee, and roasted malt with secondary elements of licorice and molasses, maybe a little bourbon. yummy.
taste follows the aroma closely with lots of the aforementioned; a touch of vanilla i missed in the nose. and while there's a splash of booziness in the finish, otherwise the 11% ABV is well-hidden. to be sure, this is a tasty, decadent brew. great mouthfeel, velvety with a medium-full body; average carbonation.
overall, well, i told myself i wouldn't be swayed by the hype but in the end? yeah this is a stellar beer. no question.
