Opened 12/26/11 to share with my father and brother in law for Christmas.
Apperance: Midnight black with nice dark tan head that lasts just a few seconds.
Smell: Absolutly wonderful. Big bourbon notes and big molasses, which I love.
Taste: It was still a bit cool on the first sip, but, still got the bourbon, licorice, and molasses and as it warmed the alcohol really came through in a very good way. Picked up a few coffee notes as well.
