4.58/5  rDev +2.2%look: 5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 4.52010 bottle poured into a snifter
Looking at this beer is exactly what I would think of when peering into an abyss....black...with a finger of dark bubbly brown head that leaves brown lacing all over the glass.
Lots of roasty coffee and chocolate here with some licorice and of course barrellzzz. Lots of vanilla and even the small amount of bourbon barrel makes an appearance. 
Drinking this thing was a treat. Very chocolatey on my first sip which was very exciting. A bitterness takes a hold all over the mouth before receding into lovely dark chocolate, espresso, and vanilla. There was not much carbonation which I wasn't expecting based on the bubbles that sprang up in the head. The Abyss has a full body and leaves you wanting more as you continue to sip it. 
Had a glass as part of Dallas Beer Week and now I want a bottle so bad. This is a great beer and a must try if you come across it. 902 charactersMattSweatshirt, Nov 16, 2011
