4.75/5  rDev +6%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 4.5On-tap at Liquid Assets in Ashland, Oregon. Assume this was the 2010 vintage, as they didn't say otherwise. Reviewed from notes.
Pours a really dark, thick, black, with a bit of deep brown at the edges. Brought to me with a minimal dark tan head. Fantastic lacing.
Smell is a feast for the nose. Wonderful dark roasted malts, with chocolate as the dominant aroma, but so much more than that. This is just about the best-smelling unadulterated stout I have ever encountered.
Taste is simply amazing. Dark roasted malts, sweet chocolate, a bit of fruit. Kinda boozy (hints of whiskey), but not unpleasantly so. A light bitterness comes on half-way through, and persists through the finish with a nicely balanced sweetness.
Mouthfeel is top-notch. Super-thick, super-heavy, but oh so creamy and wonderful. Medium carbonation, higher than many imperial stouts, and really nice.
This is one of those beers that just makes you say "wow." It is incredibly tasty, and every sip reveals more layers of subtle flavors. No sharp edges, nothing lacking. Just so much rich, sweet, boozy, dark, goodness. I took over half an hour to drink my 10-oz. pour, because I just wanted to savor every little bit of it. One of the best beers I've ever had. 1,237 characterszeledonia, Jul 02, 2011
