4.83/5  rDev +7.8%look: 5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 5Poured from 22 oz. black bottle to Oversized Wine glass. 2010 reserve with best after date of 11-15-11 on bottle. I should wait on it, but I've never had this beer before and can't wait that long to try it. $11.99 a bottle.
Appearance: Deep dark black with a large dark brown creamy head. Decent retention. Great lacing.
Smell: Bourbon, coffee, molasses, dark fruit and chocolate notes in the nose. Slight woody aroma.
