4.92/5  rDev +9.8%look: 4.5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 5There is really not much more to say about this beer, it deserves its place on BA's top ten list then some.
Wax sealed bottle, pours black as coal with a deep brown head (assuming you don't accidentally get wax in the glass... ooops).
 Smell is a strong chocolate and coffee (stout) smell, with notes of a honey and something I couldn't quite place (other reviews have said "Dark Fruit" that is a close as I can come to a description)
Taste... Wow, starts with a strong coffee taste quickly followed by subtle notes of sweet syrup, spices (i picked up cinnamon but my fellow tasters said i was crazy) and the aforementioned "dark fruit" finishes out with an oaky/smoky taste you would expect from an aged stout. Overall a great blend of flavors.
Mouth feel was creamy without the burn that can occur in imperial stouts. 
Drink ability goes down smooth enough that you can finish your glass with out even realizing. Like a good Italian wine you don't feel a thing until you stand up. I would gladly drink it all night long... and the hang over would be well worth it. 1,072 charactersbaronvonotocon, Aug 22, 2010
