4.75/5  rDev +6%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 4.52008 Vintage
I can't remember who sent me this, so thank you very much.! Served this at cellar temperature, in a snifter, from a twenty two ounce wax capped bottle. 
Appearance: The Abyss pours out a deep, dark as night black, that is similar to, well, an Abyss.. A somewhat vigorous pour resulted in two fingers of dense, creamy, coffee brown head. Great retention here, lasted almost throughout the experience. Left a thick, sticky coating of lace on the glass. What a great looking brew. 
Smell: Awesome nose on this beer. Quite complex. Deep, almost smokey malt aromas. Slight hints of coffee and chocolate. Definitely some licorice in there, and just a touch of bourbon and oak. Getting some molasses and char in the end. A bit spicey.
Taste: I didn't think this brew could get any better, but it did. Rich, complex flavors make up this beer. Very assertive roastiness starts out this beer beautifully. A bit of roasted coffee beans and some good dark chocolate. Just the slightest hoppiness. The molasses and licorice stand out a bit in the taste. Some oak and some bourbon are noticed as well. A bit smokey. Alcohol is there, but for the most part is hidden behind the thick layers of flavor. Still warms as it goes down though. This much better than fresh. 
Mouthfeel: Great thick, creamy, smooth as silk full bodied mouthfeel. Lower carbonation fits this beer perfectly.
Drinkability: Quite drinkable, but watch out. The Eleven percent ABV will get you. A very well crafted brew. 1,493 charactersjaxon53, Mar 14, 2010
