Pour pitch black. No light comes through it. No head at all.
Smells of licorice, roasted coffee, chocolate, and roasted malt. Smell is sweet and pleasing.
Taking a sip, I get an initial taste of black licorice with a nice sweetness and a taste of bourbon. Followed by chocolate, roasted coffee, roasted malt, with a tiny hint of bitterness at the end. The alcohol taste is prominent, but I expect it would be more subdued with age.
