4.63/5  rDev +3.3%look: 5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 5I am cracking open a '07 Abyss. Poured at 50F into a wine glass.
Near black color with a thick espresso head. Settles to a silky cover and leaves a nice lace. 
Nose has a complex roasted malt structure with licorice, molasses, chocolate, toffee oaky wood, bourbon and coffee. Also a good amount of floral hops and some dried figs or cherries.
The first sip delivers a very dark and earthy malt flavor. Adding to this first wave of musky sweets are dark ripe fruits, chocolate and rich dulce de leche. The flavor profile is kept in balance by a floral hop presence and roasty oak. Contributing to the bitter finish is licorice, molasses, faint bourbon and espreso. 
Thick and creamy texture kept in perfect control by delicate carbonation.
One of the most complex and complete stouts made. Very mature for its age, but will improve for many years to come. Simply delicious. 877 charactersrye726, Feb 04, 2008
