4.87/5  rDev +8.7%look: 4.5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 4.5Limited supply on this so we could only pick up two bottles at time. That's ok I went everday for a week and picked up two each time. Bwahaha take that! Poured a midnight black color. Even dark around the edges of the glass. A froathy tan head when poured that remained throughout the tasting. Surprising their wasn't as much viscous to the glass as I was expecting with such a big ABV.
The nose is rich with complex malt with chocolate, roast and a bourbon woody essence mostly. A superb balance overall. Touches of coffee, vanilla and molasses comes out as well. This is surprising as this beer is relatively fresh just getting it new from the store.
The taste is fantastic. A great mix of malty flavors with chocolate, roasted barley and some alcoholic warmth. Not over bearing with the astringent flavor but instead a smooth almost lactic quality from the licorice. The woody flavor is more subtle than the nose indicated. There also is a red wine-like flavor that comes out as it warms. Interesting enough there is a very subtle hop flavor that comes out with the bitterness and a floral finish. Nice to try this so young as if aged you probably wouldn't get this flavor at all.
The body is big, no kidding at 11%. But the surprise here for me was the smoothness of the beer and how everything just blended so well. Even the alcohol is noticeable but is blended so well. Overall this is a top 10 beer everyone should try once in their life. Guess I will keep going to the store till they run out. 1,504 charactersOxymoron, Feb 01, 2008
